article.headline: UMKC 98, Southern Utah 83
article.story: KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- Dee Ayuba and Quinton Day scored 22 points each as Missouri-Kansas City beat Southern Utah 98-83 Saturday night. Kalu Guasco had 18 points and a career-high 11 rebounds, Tim Blackwell scored 17 points and Dane Brumagin had 11 for the Kangaroos (12-13, 9-5 Mid-Continent). UMKC led just 40-39 at halftime. The Kangaroos used a 14-4 run to start the second half to take control of the game. Blackwell's short jumper with 15:07 left made it 54-43. The Thunderbirds (9-18, 7-7) had a two-game winning streak snapped. They got within 79-73 on a basket by Henry Uhegwu with 4:28 left. Uhegwu and Steve Barnes had 24 points each, and Barnes made seven 3-point shots. Ayuba had nine rebounds for UMKC and Rand Janes led the Thunderbirds with five. Day had a game-high five assists. His first assist gave him 117 for the season and made him the UMKC single-season assist leader.
